 memmed.  I feel that we do need a couple more gems and here's why:<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;Can you tl me to cs for a corpse retrieval?&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;umm, sure, I have to catch up with my group so you gotta hurry, can you come to dogle pitt?&quot;<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;i don't know where that is, I'm at the nexus stone&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;ok, I'll be right there&quot; (because trying to tell someone where you are takes longer than actually going to them sometimes)<br>
<br>
Guild: &quot;Are you coming to dulak renia?&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia /guild: &quot;on way!&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;Ok, that was cs right?&quot;<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;Yeah&quot;<br>
<br>
Sit down open book, get rid of manashield, mem tl to cs, stand up to cast<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;Ready?&quot;<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;Umm, can you levitate me?&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;umm, sure let me mem that.&quot;<br>
<br>
open book, get rid of root, mem levitate, stand up, cast lev on someone, open book, get rid of lev, mem root, standup<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;I'm in a hurry, can you tl me?&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;yeah, ready now?&quot;<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;Yeah, can you invis me too?&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia /gs: &quot;make me group leader, i gotta invis someone&quot;<br>
<br>
open book, get rid of root, mem invis, get rid of bounds of force, mem vision shift because I just know he's going to ask for a see invis next, stand up, cast vision shift on guy, invite guy to group to invis him, not taking group, oh, he's in another group<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;can you invis me and tl me? i gotta get my corpse&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;i can't invis you because you're in another group and not taking my invite&quot;<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;i invited you&quot;<br>
<br>
Guild: you coming Renia?<br>
<br>
Renia /gs: &quot;ok, dropping group for a min to invis this guy, be there in a sec&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;ok, invite me again&quot;<br>
<br>
get invite from guy, hit follow, cast invis on guy, drop group<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;ready for tl?&quot;<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;i'm losing invis already&quot;<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;ok, reinvite me&quot;<br>
<br>
get invite from guy, hit follow, cast invis on guy<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;ok, ready for tl?&quot;<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;yeah, plz hurry, i gotta get my corpse&quot;<br>
<br>
cast tl to cs on guy, waiting for him to hit the button, he's still here<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;i hit the cancel button by mistake, can you tl me again?&quot;<br>
<br>
cast tl to cs on guy, waiting for him to hit the button, he's still here<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;i'm losing invis&quot;<br>
<br>
cast invis on guy, waiting . . . he's still here<br>
<br>
Renia: &quot;take the tl&quot;<br>
<br>
Someone: &quot;i was losing invis so i cancelled it&quot;<br>
<br>
cast tl on guy<br>
<br>
Renia &quot;take the tl, do not hit cancel!&quot;<br>
<br>
guy finally goes away, run butt off to find group. Get into first fight and wow, how did so many get pulled?<br>
<br>
Go to hit the snare and why isn't the mob being snared? what? i'm invising the mob? geez, blast the damn thing, hit the ice comet, mob hitting Renia, ouch, mob pounds through manaskin, Krugin gets aggro off Renia, go to put manaskin back on since life is half way and everyone's fighting, manaskin not going back on, did someone put a buff on me that doesn't let me put manaskin on myself? mob pounding on Renia, Renia gets healed, mob gets pulled off Renia, Renia decides better to try to blast mob, mob comes back and smacks Renia around, need that damned manaskin! cast manaskin again, what's this? I can't tl myself? I'm not trying to tl myself, geez, forgot to change my spells up, sit down to put manaskin on, mob comes over and pounds Renia, Renia tries to stand up but sits down because mob pounded her and made her stand, she tries to stand up but the same thing happens, finally she manages to stay standing, mob pounds Renia stopping her from casting, Krugin yelling at renia for taking aggro again, Krugin tries to heal Renia, mob pounds Renia, Renia dies and is in pok<br>
<br>
Krugin tries to lay hands on corpse of Renia, Krugin yells at Renia for dying too soon. <br>
<br>
Someone: can you tl me?<br>
<br>
Renia: NO!<br>
<br>
Actually, Iwould tl the person coming to ask but I'd be muttering about my death the whole time.  Krugin actually yells at me by the way as he is my brother and sits in the same room while we play.<br>
<br>
Has any other wizard ever experienced a scenario like this or am I really the only one who forgets to change their spells up on occassion? <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
Baroness of MoY who aspires to greatness (and may attain it one day).</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=corinia>Corinia</A> at: 4/24/03 2:49:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bayler>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/03 4:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something That Happens Too Often to a Forgetful Wizard</span><hr size=1> It sounds to me like the problem is mostly that you're too kind to morons when you're in a hurry.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
Tessally - 53nd flicker Nun of Solusek Ro - Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=corinia>Corinia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/03 4:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something That Happens Too Often to a Forgetful Wizard</span><hr size=1> Heh, that's just a worse case scenario of tling someone.  Most people aren't that bad although there have been a few.  I've had times where I've done the tls and just forgot to change the spells up and then when I get into a combat situation I'm trying to invis myself or something. <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
Baroness of MoY who aspires to greatness (and may attain it one day).</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eedelia01>Eedelia01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 1:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something That Happens Too Often to a Forgetful Wizard</span><hr size=1> Honestly, we should get an AA ability that lets us get another spell gem at the least. At the most they should give us one, Think about it- My line up is Nuke Nuke Lesser Nuke or Xuxl...then i have Fetter, Snare, Harvest Abscond. I can think of a billion other things to do with just one other gem. Like..Stun! or Evac! You know how annoying it is when you load evac and everyone else starts running for the zoneline or the &quot;click out&quot; and your standing there casting evac like a retard? or how about the fact that Virtue keeps you from that evac? oh yeah...now you need a gate of some sort..oh by the way, you have 4 mobs hitting you....<br>
<br>
1 extra spell gem.......come on! please!!? =D <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=corinia>Corinia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 11:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something That Happens Too Often to a Forgetful Wizard</span><hr size=1> Hey, get a crucible of escape.  My brother is a gm potter and he made me one.  They are druid and wizard useable and take just as long as lesser evac to use.  I don't use evac in the gems because I have it. <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
Baroness of MoY who aspires to greatness (and may attain it one day).</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lykanlyteheart>lykan lyteheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 3:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something That Happens Too Often to a Forgetful Wizard</span><hr size=1> I really like when we're deep in seb and evac to pick up a group member, and I port us to ej instead <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> P<br>
<br>
I usally have the very last (bottom) spell slot saved for evac wether it be personal or for a group.<br>
<br>
I the second slot from the bottom is what i call the &quot;dummy slot&quot; meaning there is never anything in the slot worth a darn or important to my survive-ability.<br>
<br>
When asked for a tl, i drop to the ground, de-mem whatever is in there (steel skin, mansink, last tl I did etc). Throw TL in the slot and shoot them off.<br>
<br>
Since its my dummy slot I dont have to worry about re meming anything in its place, I just leave whatever I put in there last. Sometimes TL to bind is in there for days at a time unused. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=corinia>Corinia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 4:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something That Happens Too Often to a Forgetful Wizard</span><hr size=1> I keep harvest in the second to the last slot.  Whenever harvest pops and I need mana, I use it.  I never demem harvest.  My dummy slot - tls, invises, levs, evacs, ports - goes in my last slot.  I have not yet decided what to do with the third from the bottom.  I always kept manaskin there.  I used to go through peridots like crazy (mostly because I prefer to live) in fights.  I just got my epic last night and can't wait to get into a fight now.  Woo hoo! <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
Baroness of MoY who aspires to greatness (and may attain it one day).</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm42.showPrevMessage?topicID=61.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm42.showNextMessage?topicID=61.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm42.emailToFriend?topicID=61.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm42.threadControl?topicID=61.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm42.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=61.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm42.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=61.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm60">Graffe Forum News<option 